				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">At one point in time I had two NES's because someone sent one for Christmas after I already had one.  On the older NES, the default screen color (seen when no game was loaded or during the few split-seconds before a game drew the title screen) was light blue.  On the newer NES, the screen color was pinkish (don't remember exactly how it looked - that NES kicked the bucket years ago and we threw it out).  Strangely, Legend of Zelda got a different result - during the second or so it takes to boot, the older NES would flash two or three different colors on the screen before the title screen.  I haven't found any emulators that show this, and I don't remember it ever happening when starting LOZ with a Game Genie (which blackens the screen before starting the game, and no colors showed up before the title screen).  To this day I've wondered what it was about LOZ that caused the NES to show multiple screen colors during the bootup phase.  None of the colors matched the background color of the title screen.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

